# These Data are copyrighted and use in a publication requires written permission
# as detailed in our Terms of use:  https://lter.kbs.msu.edu/data/terms-of-use/
# Use of the data constitutes acceptance of the terms.
#     VARIATE TABLE
# year		sample year
# treatment		treatment that was sampled
# replicate		replicate plot that was sampled
# station		station within the plot that was sampled
# core		core identifier for the station (generally two cores were taken per station)
# section		horizon section (cores were divided into surface
column2: middle and deep sections pre 2013 and by depth in 2013)

column1: # horizon_length	centimeter	length of the horizon sampled
# core_volume_cm3	cubicCentimeter	core volume of the section
# gravel_free_bulk_density	gramsPerCubicCentimeter	bulk density of the gravel free portion of the soil (gravel >4 mm	removed)
# total_bulk_density	gramsPerCubicCentimeter	bulk density (including any gravel)
# gravel_weight_g	gram
# comments		any observations relating to this core
#        DATA TABLE CORRECTIONS AND COMMENTS
#2019-1-16 Sven Bohm. For the 2013 samples the dry weights were incorrectly calculated as wet * (1-moisture) when it should have been wet /(1+moisture) . The error has been corrected.
#2019-1-18 Sven Bohm. re include the gravel free bulk density in the output.
#2019-6-25. Sven Bohm. The 2001 samples mistakenly used the tube diameter instead of the cutting head diameter to calculate  the volume for the bulk density
column2: The tube diameter was 6.6 cm while the cutting head diameter as 6 cm . This resulted in much lower bulk densities (since the volume was bigger) The error has been corrected.
